            }
        ],
        "cbStatement": "Presents a study of people’s experiences with FutureMe—a slow messaging technology used for 12 years by over 1 million people. Findings illustrated many outcomes from profound reminiscence to unsettling encounters. ",
        "keywords": "Slow Technology; Temporality; Reflection; Memories. ",
        "venue": "Paper",
        "subtype": "Paper",
        "award": 0,
        "hm": 0
